  m_Name: Editor Tooling
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: ModularForge.Trailback.Demo::ModularForge.Trailback.Demo.Features.FeatureDemoData
  featureName: Editor Tooling
  shortDescription: Create and configure common Trailback components directly from
    Unity editor menus.
  fullDescription: "Trailback includes built-in editor tooling designed to streamline
    setup and reduce manual scene configuration.\n\nCreate common Trailback components
    directly from Unity's context menus:\n\n\u2022 Complete Setup\n\u2022 Legacy
    Back Input Source\n\u2022 Input System Back Input Source\n\u2022 Trailback Event
    Listener\n\u2022 Runtime Monitor\n\nEditor tooling helps developers quickly bootstrap
    a Trailback integration and provides a consistent starting point for new scenes.\n\nThe
    generated components are fully editable and can be customized to fit existing
    project architecture and workflows.\n\nDesigned to reduce repetitive setup tasks
    while keeping the framework flexible and framework-agnostic."
